# CLAUDE.md - B2B SaaS Example (Compliance Automation)

> This is a filled-in example showing what CLAUDE.md looks like for a B2B SaaS product.
> Copy the blank template from CLAUDE.md.example and adapt it to your product.

## Shipwright

Type `/start` at the beginning of a session to launch the Shipwright orchestrator.

## Product

- **Name:** ComplianceOS
- **Category:** B2B SaaS compliance automation platform
- **Stage:** Growth (Series A, 18 months post-launch)
- **Target users:** Compliance officers and CTOs at mid-market fintech companies (100-1000 employees) who need SOC 2, PCI-DSS, or HIPAA certification
- **Core job-to-be-done:** Reduce the time and cost of achieving and maintaining compliance certifications from months of manual work to weeks of guided automation

## Key Metrics

| Metric | Current Value | Target | Timeframe |
|---|---|---|---|
| North Star: Frameworks completed per quarter | 42 | 80 | Q3 2026 |
| Time to first framework completion | 47 days | 30 days | Q3 2026 |
| Net revenue retention | 108% | 120% | Q4 2026 |
| NPS | 34 | 45 | Q4 2026 |

## Strategic Priorities (Current Quarter)

1. **Multi-framework support:** Ship PCI-DSS alongside existing SOC 2 and HIPAA. 60% of pipeline is blocked on this.
2. **Evidence auto-collection:** Integrate with AWS, GCP, and GitHub to pull compliance evidence automatically instead of requiring manual uploads.
3. **Enterprise pilot:** Close 3 design partners above 500 employees. Current sweet spot is 100-300 and we need to move upmarket.

## What We're NOT Doing

- Self-serve onboarding. Our ACV is $45K and customers expect white-glove setup. Not worth automating yet.
- International frameworks (GDPR, ISO 27001). US-only until multi-framework is proven.
- Building our own audit marketplace. We partner with existing firms.

## Personas

### Compliance Officer Carmen
- **Role:** Head of Compliance, reports to General Counsel. Owns audit readiness and policy maintenance.
- **Goals:** Pass audits on the first attempt, reduce the evidence scramble before audit season, maintain continuous compliance between audits.
- **Pain points:** Evidence is scattered across 12 tools. Engineers ignore her requests for documentation. She's managing compliance in spreadsheets.
- **How she evaluates tools:** Needs to see her specific framework supported. Cares about auditor acceptance of generated evidence. Asks for customer references in her industry.

### CTO Dev
- **Role:** CTO or VP Engineering. Signs the contract. Cares about compliance as a business blocker, not a passion project.
- **Goals:** Unblock enterprise deals that require SOC 2. Minimize engineering time spent on compliance tasks.
- **Pain points:** Engineers spend 2 weeks per quarter on compliance busywork. Audit prep derails roadmap every time.

## Competitors

| Competitor | Type | Our Advantage | Their Advantage |
|---|---|---|---|
| Vanta | Direct | Deeper evidence auto-collection, better multi-framework overlap detection | Brand recognition, larger integration library |
| Drata | Direct | More flexible policy templates, better mid-market pricing | Stronger enterprise sales motion |
| Manual consulting firms | Indirect | 3x faster, continuous monitoring vs. point-in-time | Trusted relationships, auditor familiarity |

## Conventions

- **User stories:** "As a [persona], I want [action] so that [outcome]"
- **PRD format:** Working Backwards (press release first)
- **Prioritization:** RICE scoring, with reach defined as number of affected customer accounts
- **Roadmap style:** Now / Next / Later
- **Sprint cadence:** 2-week sprints
- **Definition of Done:** Feature deployed to staging, automated tests passing, docs updated, compliance impact assessed

## Tools & Integrations

- **Project management:** Linear
- **Documentation:** Notion
- **Analytics:** Amplitude + internal Postgres dashboards
- **Communication:** Slack
- **Design:** Figma
- **CRM:** Salesforce

## Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| Framework | A compliance standard (SOC 2, HIPAA, PCI-DSS) |
| Evidence | Documentation or system output proving a control is in place |
| Control | A specific security or process requirement within a framework |
| CAB | Customer Advisory Board, quarterly meeting with 8 design partners |
| ACV | Annual contract value |
